[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Determining library dependencies**\n\nI'm looking into whether the library requires additional setup beyond the usual test scaffold. It seems the documentation mentions that cookies aren't necessary, but WebClientSession may use them. I need to find out if jackson-databind is needed for testing, but existing tests use only jackson-core, and for standard usage, no extra dependency is required. OAuth2 is optional for the auth client, but the library's vertx-auth-oauth2 could be used. I'm also considering if meaningful coverage is reachable with the current setup.\n\n**Verifying test setup**\n\nI’m figuring out that tests can run on JVM without problems, but the native image setup requires system properties. The environment must generate tests that include these properties. Since the driver can apply deterministic dependencies, I need guidance on setting runtime arguments for version 5.0.1, possibly broader for Netty 4.2.2 on Java 25 for native runs. I might verify if existing code fails, but running the test with 5.0.1 could be costly. I also need to check the metadata for more insights.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_06cb614d6fba019a016a4143b2a1e881968e58cad2f8617c8b\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQUO6_yV_oxILRISZiSWz8eiY9Ra2st2y7IDxW58oJ_zRDs_LbwfiMpcZtX3tb00KvrWZVEbwXgdFX1G-OVqVJeZux8kNadfq2ESWoMgYpA2lJOKcQl7SnED61pirX7aaws_uC0hF7NBG7G1JyZerJCtRS9KvWsuqA1Qsd_cXQ-yimVnPiZEfBJIJiTqzT7rfQiLERDMiuL8ri_L_96IyPUAl1WZvtZO_5Sk3duLK_BwccmNSkpDmSALoRVDIY_Cr_0DSgttsn_ncl-RkKkg0LNV6BV1EmiXNVfdH_MCayAViK-X6Sxv3YRr4QkBYCwgYH7t_-HNs2k12Us8mC5vHohXeM0N65LHvfZqsZWOHPe0dGE2Dk_AjmB1oG4jUFlWFc7KfBFv8pFJdbBaWh_bJSulwISYJ0yLEKQ1nNrxyIyeGwaiBZJaZ7__m0sghF_xbF-EtQ-wUIMacNBSEznK_WEookYW-Nu9YEFDvE9JrRSZmSwc73tK8fIcriGUZ6QNjMn5O0dZNofgfris5koEmJu3tge5Bb0tBUmiE5SgsGI6T8cZVOYNsf3Zx7G60qk2sjN18YwFAuYVE-WeZjA6V1ZExssQ4eZHtq4T07fKoALQyCRy2P