ive test execution of 5.0.1, ensure the generated build/test setup applies runtime system properties `-Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow` and `-Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true`; the existing 5.0.0 scaffold has these behind a 5.0.0-only guard, so extend/generalize that guard for 5.0.1 or Netty 4.2.x. Keep meaningful tests self-contained with a local Vert.x `HttpServer` on loopback; no external service environment is required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"If generated tests choose optional features such as OAuth2-specific flows or POJO databind body codecs, they may introduce additional dependency needs, but those are not required for meaningful core Web Client coverage.\",\n    \"Local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative for whether the Netty unsafe-access properties are sufficient on the exact JDK/native-image mode.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_06cb614d6fba019a016a4143cdbdb881968d1b779b5d5279dc\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 702, "output": 965, "cacheRead": 26624, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28291, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782662081540, "responseId": "resp_06cb614d6fba019a016a4143c2305c81969c34c95425f43e8f"}}
